Based on the provided excerpts, the primary purpose of control AU-2 (Event Logging) is to identify, specify, and coordinate the types of events that a system is capable of logging in order to support the audit function and after-the-fact investigations of incidents [3]. Specifically, the control requires organizations to:

* Identify the types of events the system is capable of logging to support the audit function [3];
* Coordinate the event logging function with other organizational entities requiring audit-related information to guide and inform the selection criteria for events to be logged [3];
* Specify the event types to be logged along with the frequency or situation requiring logging for each [3];
* Provide a rationale for why the selected event types are adequate to support after-the-fact investigations of incidents [3]; and
* Review and update the selected event types at an organization-defined frequency to ensure they remain relevant and continue to support the needs of the organization [3].
